# MacOS X Button Setup
# Written by Maciej Delmanowski <harnir@linux.net.pl>
# Maintained and updated by Dominique Michel <dominique_libre@users.sourceforge,net>
#
# This is the window titlebar button setup similar to the MacOS X
# buttons on the titlebar
# Additional support for NumLock key

# third button - various ways to maximize a window
Mouse 1 5 $[Mod0]2	Window-Button-Function Button5 /Window-Menu-Maximize Maximize
Mouse 2 5 $[Mod0]2	Window-Button-Function Button5 /Window-Menu-Maximize Maximize 0 100
Mouse 3 5 $[Mod0]2	Window-Button-Function Button5 /Window-Menu-Maximize Maximize 100 0
Mouse 1 5 $[Mod1]2	Window-Button-Function Button5 /Window-Menu-Maximize Maximize grow grow
Mouse 2 5 $[Mod1]2	Window-Button-Function Button5 /Window-Menu-Maximize Maximize 0 grow
Mouse 3 5 $[Mod1]2	Window-Button-Function Button5 /Window-Menu-Maximize Maximize grow 0

# vim:ft=fvwm
